<li><strong>Re-run ŌĆ£docxŌåÆpdf swapŌĆØ again</strong> (now that the converted PDFs are inside <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">forlitrev_pdfs</code>)</li>
<li><strong>Run GROBID batch again (incremental) to generate TEIs for the newly added PDFs</strong></li>
<li><strong>Recompute includedŌåÆTEI coverage</strong></li>
<li>Then we do <strong>categorisation + exclusion suggestions</strong> (without overwriting your current <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">include_final</code> until you approve)</li>
</ol>
<p>Below are the commands/scripts to do steps 1ŌĆō5 now.</p>
<hr>
<h1>Step 1 ŌĆö Build a duplicate ŌĆ£dropŌåÆkeepŌĆØ map (deterministic, logged)</h1>
<p>WeŌĆÖll choose the <strong>canonical (keep) filename</strong> per hash using a rule that matches your project reality:</p>
<ul>
<li>Prefer filenames that start with <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">10_</code> (these align with your <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">paper_id</code>/DOI-style naming and are easiest to reference later)</li>
<li>If none starts with <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">10_</code>, keep the shortest filename (usually the cleanest)</li>
</ul>
<p>Run this in <strong>PowerShell</strong> from project root:</p>
