<p>Why this is the correct minimal fix (based on your script): your current <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">doi_from_filename()</code> runs on <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">name.replace("_","/")</code> where <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">name</code> still includes <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">.tei.xml</code>, and <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">DOI_RE</code> allows <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">.</code> so it can match through the extension; then <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">norm_doi()</code> doesnŌĆÖt remove it. <span class="inline-flex p-0.5" data-state="closed"><a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://gist.github.com/Achionye/ca782340e7ab67d7a152c94c00717185" class="focus-visible:ring-ring inline-flex rounded-sm no-underline focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2"><span class="bg-surface-raised inline-flex h-4 w-4 items-center justify-center rounded-sm p-0.5 cursor-pointer"><span class="text-center font-['Inter'] text-[10px] font-normal leading-3 text-interactive-link">1</span></span></a></span></p>
