<h2>Step 2 ŌĆö Remove the DOI dependency ceiling using <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">primary_file</code> (your registry already supports this)</h2>
<p>Your registry header shows you already store <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">primary_file</code> per paper. ThatŌĆÖs perfect: for TEIs generated from <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">forlitrev_pdfs</code>, the TEI filename is deterministically <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">PDF_STEM + ".tei.xml"</code> in <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">.\fulltext_tei_from_pdfs_v1\</code>.</p>
