<h2>Step 5C ŌĆö Make the project ŌĆ£not limitedŌĆØ: add a fallback linker that does NOT depend on DOI existing in TEI</h2>
<p>Even with better normalization, some TEIs genuinely wonŌĆÖt contain the DOI anywhere (publisher layout, DOI only on a cover page, or stripped). DOI-only linking will always leave some behind.</p>
<p>So we add one small new step: <strong>link included papers to TEI by PDF stem (and title if needed)</strong>.</p>
<h3>Why PDF-stem linking is reliable in <em>your</em> pipeline</h3>
<p>Your batch extractor writes TEIs as:</p>
<p><code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">outdir / (p.stem + ".tei.xml")</code> <span class="inline-flex p-0.5" data-state="closed"><a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://gist.github.com/Achionye/ca782340e7ab67d7a152c94c00717185" class="focus-visible:ring-ring inline-flex rounded-sm no-underline focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2"><span class="bg-surface-raised inline-flex h-4 w-4 items-center justify-center rounded-sm p-0.5 cursor-pointer"><span class="text-center font-['Inter'] text-[10px] font-normal leading-3 text-interactive-link">1</span></span></a></span></p>
<p>So for the PDFs that succeeded, there is a deterministic TEI path by stemŌĆöno DOI required.</p>
<h3>Create a new script: <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">scripts/link_included_to_tei_by_pdfstem_v1.py</code></h3>
<p>This script will:</p>
<ul>
<li>read <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">study_registry_SCREENING_WORKING.csv</code></li>
<li>for each included record, try to locate its PDF (if your registry has a <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">pdf</code>/<code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">pdf_name</code>/<code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">file</code> column; if not, it will fall back to ŌĆ£search by DOI-in-filenameŌĆØ and finally ŌĆ£search by title keywordŌĆØ)</li>
<li>then map to <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">fulltext_tei_from_pdfs_v1\&lt;pdf_stem&gt;.tei.xml</code></li>
<li>output <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">out_synthesis_filtered_full_v1\included_tei_linkmap_v1.csv</code></li>
</ul>
