n></div></div><div class="no-scrollbar relative flex w-full flex-1 flex-col overflow-x-auto transition-[max-height] duration-300"><div class="min-w-0"><div class="flex flex-col gap-3"><div class="border-border-faint flex w-full flex-col rounded-md border p-3"><div class="flex items-center gap-2"><svg width="1.5em" height="1.5em" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" color="currentColor" class="text-interactive-normal h-4 w-4"><path d="M22 12C22 6.47715 17.5228 2 12 2C6.47715 2 2 6.47715 2 12C2 17.5228 6.47715 22 12 22" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path><path d="M13 2.04932C13 2.04932 16 5.99994 16 11.9999" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path><path d="M11 21.9506C11 21.9506 8 17.9999 8 11.9999C8 5.99994 11 2.04932 11 2.04932" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path><path d="M2.62964 15.5H12" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path><path d="M2.62964 8.5H21.3704" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M21.8789 17.9174C22.3727 18.2211 22.3423 18.9604 21.8337 19.0181L19.2671 19.309L18.1159 21.6213C17.8878 22.0795 17.1827 21.8552 17.0661 21.2873L15.8108 15.1713C15.7123 14.6913 16.1437 14.3892 16.561 14.646L21.8789 17.9174Z" stroke="currentColor"></path></svg><div class="text-interactive-normal text-sm">No Sources</div></div></div><div class="prose prose-sm prose-pre:bg-transparent prose-pre:p-0 text-wrap break-words"><p>What you have right now is <strong>the Docker client</strong> (<code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">docker.exe</code>) but <strong>not the Docker daemon/engine</strong>. ThatŌĆÖs why <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">docker version</code> prints the client info and then fails with:</p>
<blockquote>
<p><code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">failed to connect to the docker API ... dockerDesktopLinuxEngine</code></p>
</blockquote>
<p>Your <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">grobid_0.8.2.1-crf.tar</code> is almost certainly a <strong>Docker image tarball</strong> (an offline/exported image). ItŌĆÖs <em>not</em> a Windows executable GROBID server by itself. You can use it <strong>only after the Docker engine is running</strong>, via <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">docker load -i ...</code>.</p>
<p>So the immediate goal is: <strong>start a GROBID HTTP server at <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">http://127.0.0.1:8070</code></strong> (because your scripts call that endpoint).</p>
<hr>
<h1>Step 1 ŌĆö Start Docker Desktop <em>properly</em> (PowerShell, no guessing)</h1>
<h2>1A) Check if the Docker Desktop Windows service exists and start it</h2>
