;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent" src="https://arena.ai/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fopengraph.githubassets.com%2Fd8afcab91e47a700cb80740afa0099f252b19156bdb4ae019869b00cc5c2db92%2FgrobidOrg%2Fgrobid-client-python&amp;w=3840&amp;q=85"></div></a></div></div></div></div><div class="prose prose-sm prose-pre:bg-transparent prose-pre:p-0 text-wrap break-words"><p>That <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">docker ps</code> error means <strong>there is no Docker daemon running on your machine right now</strong>, so there is <strong>no way a Docker-based GROBID server could be running</strong> (at least not via Docker Desktop). Until a GROBID <strong>HTTP service</strong> is running at <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">http://127.0.0.1:8070</code>, your scripts that call <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">/api/processFulltextDocument</code> will fail. <span class="inline-flex p-0.5" data-state="closed"><a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://deepwiki.com/kermitt2/grobid/3-installation-and-deployment" class="focus-visible:ring-ring inline-flex rounded-sm no-underline focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2"><span class="bg-surface-raised inline-flex h-4 w-4 items-center justify-center rounded-sm p-0.5 cursor-pointer"><span class="text-center font-['Inter'] text-[10px] font-normal leading-3 text-interactive-link">1</span></span></a></span></p>
