<p>send PDFs to an endpoint like:</p>
<ul>
<li><code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">http://127.0.0.1:8070/api/processFulltextDocument</code></li>
</ul>
<p>So ŌĆ£having GROBID locallyŌĆØ only helps if the <strong>server is actually running and listening on port 8070</strong> at the moment you start the batch. The quick <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">Invoke-WebRequest http://127.0.0.1:8070</code> check is just a 2ŌĆæsecond guard that prevents you from launching a long batch run that would otherwise fail 375 times with connection errors.</p>
