<h2>1) <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">--secret</code> is not a valid flag (because ŌĆ£secretŌĆØ is the default)</h2>
<p>Your <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">gh</code> output literally says:</p>
<ul>
<li><code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">-p, --public  List the gist publicly (default "secret")</code></li>
</ul>
<p>So:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Secret gist = default</strong> ŌåÆ donŌĆÖt pass anything</li>
<li>Public gist ŌåÆ add <code class="rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-surface-tertiary font-mono text-[0.9em] text-text-primary font-medium" node="[object Object]">--public</code></li>
</ul>
<p>That part is normal.</p>
