<li><strong>Audit layer</strong> (you already started): discrepancy scans + stratified manual checks <span class="inline-flex p-0.5" data-state="closed"><a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://gist.github.com/Achionye/14f8232e3c597c997be21fd52ee2c71f" class="focus-visible:ring-ring inline-flex rounded-sm no-underline focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2"><span class="bg-surface-raised inline-flex h-4 w-4 items-center justify-center rounded-sm p-0.5 cursor-pointer"><span class="text-center font-['Inter'] text-[10px] font-normal leading-3 text-interactive-link">1</span></span></a></span></li>
</ul>
<p>That architecture is what makes the project ŌĆ£not limitedŌĆØ: you can always (1) retrieve the exact source text, (2) re-extract fields, (3) re-audit, (4) regenerate tables/figuresŌĆöwithout re-reading 268 papers end-to-end.</p>
